https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc7030#section-4.5.2

Here's the object to convert to CDDL, if someone gets inspired: (@cabo ?)

   CsrAttrs ::= SEQUENCE SIZE (0..MAX) OF AttrOrOID

   AttrOrOID ::= CHOICE (oid OBJECT IDENTIFIER, attribute Attribute }

   Attribute { ATTRIBUTE:IOSet } ::= SEQUENCE {
        type   ATTRIBUTE.&id({IOSet}),
        values SET SIZE(1..MAX) OF ATTRIBUTE.&Type({IOSet}{@type}) }

Another update, removing specifications only targeting X.509:
https://github.com/cose-wg/CBOR-certificates/pull/231/files

@malishav With the last table entry, it is intended to be able to request a URI, but it doesn't distinguish between c5u and x5u. 

@cabo Please sanity check table at the end of the link above. Would it be appropriate to specify a dedicated Content-Format for a URI to a C509 certificate (as opposed to a URI to a x.509 certificate)?

@gselander to 
*add brief mention of ~"such as in self signed certificates"
*strengthen the wording to make it mandatory (us accepting the small increase in complexity)
